T0	Participants 0 41	Veterans Affairs congestive heart failure
T1	Participants 222 288	patients with congestive heart failure and ventricular arrhythmia.
T2	Participants 356 499	Eligible patients include those with ischemic and nonischemic congestive heart failure and with > or = 10 ventricular premature beats per hour.
T3	Participants 500 752	All patients must have shortness of breath with minimal exertion or paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnea, a left ventricular internal dimension (LVIDd) by echocardiogram of > or = 55 mm or a cardiothoracic ratio of > 0.5 and an ejection fraction of < or = 40%.
T4	Participants 833 926	Patients will be entered into the study for 2.5 years and followed for an additional 2 years.
T5	Participants 1101 1175	674 patients will be entered into the study from 25 participating centers.